Text: @elonmusk @GerberKawasaki @thirdrowtesla Come to a rural community like El Dorado County where a large Manufacture like Tesla will be appreciated. We would all welcome an entrepreneur with similar feelings about civil liberties and the right of business owners.

In El Dorado County we would be appreciative of a large manufacture like Tesla bringing considerable jobs and tax revenue. Let progressives in the Bay enjoy your products and fellow Conservatives enjoy the economic strength. Come out to our county and see the possibilities.

@JBradleyBurnett @Benzel4Congress According to many of my constituents, McClintock has received their vote 4 years because they felt he was their only choice for a republican candidate. In my running I am offering my constituents another choice.

@JBradleyBurnett @Benzel4Congress Much of the community that I have spoken with rallies behind the opportunity to support one of their own rather than an outsider who does not live in or was born in our district.

@JBradleyBurnett @Benzel4Congress I was born and raised in my district and truly have their interests and needs at heart. I believe it would be inappropriate for me to presume that I can better represent another congressional district then their current representation or other local candidates.

@JBradleyBurnett @Benzel4Congress Hello RedCal, I am running as a Republican. I'm running against Tom McClintock to represent California's 4th congressional district because I believe District should be represented by one of their own people.

@Benzel4Congress Julianne, I have received no invitation to the debate at William Jessup University. I am not certain how you have been reaching out to the cannidates, however you are welcome to send information to Jacobthomas4congress2020@gmail.com and I will consider your invite.
